This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with improving the performance of LSTM-RNNs for speech recognition tasks. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it proposes a new architecture for deep learning models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) because it deals with speech recognition, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it proposes a new neural network architecture, and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because it deals with processing sequential data.
